00:00:10.029 --> 00:00:10.997 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:00:12.031 --> 00:00:12.999 position:33% line:89% align:start
uh... uh...

00:00:17.204 --> 00:00:18.105 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:00:35.592 --> 00:00:38.562 position:10% line:5% align:start
(AKARI) <i>Why are they going </i>
 <i>after the serum... and not us?</i>

00:00:40.197 --> 00:00:41.565 position:5% line:5% align:start
 <i>Could they...?</i>

00:00:44.736 --> 00:00:46.404 position:16% line:5% align:start
 <i>Do they know who we are?</i>

00:00:53.178 --> 00:00:54.213 position:33% line:89% align:start
[panicking]

00:00:54.246 --> 00:00:55.014 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:00:55.047 --> 00:00:56.081 position:41% line:89% align:start
[thud]

00:00:56.115 --> 00:01:03.190 position:5% line:5% align:start
[groaning and nervous breathing]

00:01:07.093 --> 00:01:09.864 position:5% line:5% align:start
 <i>(AKARI) Is this what the Bugs 2</i>
 <i>crew were faced with?</i>

00:01:12.533 --> 00:01:14.001 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:01:14.937 --> 00:01:18.440 position:24% line:89% align:start
[insect chirping]

00:01:19.541 --> 00:01:20.877 position:19% line:89% align:start
No! Eva! Get up! Run!

00:01:20.910 --> 00:01:22.879 position:16% line:89% align:start
Eva! Hurry! Get up! Run!

00:01:22.912 --> 00:01:26.917 position:7% line:89% align:start
[gasping, holding back tears]

00:01:26.951 --> 00:01:28.786 position:5% line:5% align:start
(AKARI) <i>How long have they been</i>
 <i>hiding? </i>

00:01:29.620 --> 00:01:31.188 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>How the hell did they get in?</i>

00:01:31.222 --> 00:01:36.293 position:24% line:89% align:start
[hyperventilating]

00:01:36.327 --> 00:01:37.462 position:16% line:89% align:start
[grunt, heavy breathing]

00:01:41.701 --> 00:01:44.102 position:13% line:5% align:start
 <i>And who the hell are they</i>
 <i>taking orders from?</i>

00:01:46.138 --> 00:01:47.807 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chirping]

00:03:18.811 --> 00:03:23.849 position:33% line:5% align:start
03  TO MARS

00:03:23.882 --> 00:03:25.752 position:5% line:5% align:start
(COMMANDER) <i>What? Back to Earth?</i>

00:03:27.921 --> 00:03:31.926 position:10% line:71% align:start
That's right. And we'll be
taking all of the remaining
Terraformars that are onboard
with us as samples.

00:03:32.125 --> 00:03:34.929 position:5% line:83% align:start
Mission manual, check. Return to
Earth, initiated.

00:03:35.396 --> 00:03:37.064 position:21% line:89% align:start
[grunts and banging]

00:03:37.098 --> 00:03:38.967 position:24% line:89% align:start
Come on! Open up!

00:03:39.367 --> 00:03:41.803 position:10% line:5% align:start
(COMMANDER) <i>I'm afraid not,</i>
 <i>Captain Komachi.</i>

00:03:42.370 --> 00:03:44.806 position:5% line:5% align:start
 <i>Six samples isn't going to cut </i>
 <i>it. </i>

00:03:46.843 --> 00:03:46.876 position:10% line:5% align:start
 <i>Twenty years of funding and</i>
 <i>the survival of the human race</i>
 <i>depend upon this</i>
 <i>mission'ssuccess. </i>

00:03:50.413 --> 00:03:54.417 position:13% line:5% align:start
 <i>Failure is not an option.</i>
 <i>Continue with Plan Delta.</i>

00:03:54.450 --> 00:03:55.618 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:03:57.955 --> 00:04:02.226 position:5% line:77% align:start
But sir, Plan Delta is supposed
to be for mission return
failures only.

00:04:04.729 --> 00:04:06.163 position:21% line:89% align:start
[nervous breathing]

00:04:06.196 --> 00:04:07.032 position:24% line:5% align:start
[insect chirpping]

00:04:09.802 --> 00:04:13.739 position:5% line:5% align:start
(COMMANDER) <i>Captain Komachi, You</i>
 <i>must trust in the fortitude of</i>
 <i>the officers. Those of high</i>
 <i>rank can protect the others...</i>

00:04:13.773 --> 00:04:15.474 position:24% line:5% align:start
 <i>and complete this</i>
 <i>mission.</i>

00:04:15.508 --> 00:04:16.877 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sigh]

00:04:19.345 --> 00:04:24.651 position:5% line:71% align:start
I've seen what those things can
do to a ship at take off, but
we're nowhere near Mars's
surface.

00:04:25.787 --> 00:04:31.325 position:5% line:71% align:start
We're high in the thermosphere!
It'd be impossible for them to
gain access to the ship from
this far away!

00:04:32.161 --> 00:04:36.231 position:5% line:77% align:start
But somehow they've boarded! Or
is it that they've been hiding
here all along?!

00:04:36.465 --> 00:04:40.335 position:10% line:77% align:start
 <i>It doesn't make sense! But </i>
 <i>telling you bastards is a waste</i>
 <i>of time!</i>

00:04:42.338 --> 00:04:44.841 position:7% line:83% align:start
Someone is controlling these
damn roaches!

00:04:45.408 --> 00:04:46.977 position:35% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:04:51.082 --> 00:04:51.716 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:04:55.854 --> 00:04:56.855 position:30% line:5% align:start
 <i>We're falling.</i>

00:05:02.995 --> 00:05:05.031 position:7% line:89% align:start
(KOU HONDA) <i>M.A.R.S. Rankings?</i>

00:05:07.034 --> 00:05:09.870 position:5% line:77% align:start
(SHICHISEI HIRUMA) <i>Yes. Rankings</i>
 <i>have been assigned according</i>
 <i>to  each crew member's ability. </i>

00:05:12.206 --> 00:05:17.212 position:7% line:71% align:start
 <i>Those ranking the highest were</i>
 <i>made officers. Under Capatian</i>
 <i>Komachi, there are six </i>
 <i>officers.</i>

00:05:17.277 --> 00:05:19.114 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>They are our main weapons.</i>

00:05:20.982 --> 00:05:21.983 position:38% line:89% align:start
Weapons?

00:05:23.284 --> 00:05:26.222 position:16% line:83% align:start
Yes. Very powerful and
dangerous weapons.

00:05:29.391 --> 00:05:31.393 position:5% line:83% align:start
(JOSEPH) <i>That's a bit unwieldy, </i>
 <i>isn't it, Michelle? </i>

00:05:32.528 --> 00:05:34.397 position:5% line:83% align:start
Why don't you let me give you a
hand?

00:05:36.533 --> 00:05:39.070 position:7% line:83% align:start
(SHICHISEI) <i>The officers will</i>
 <i>lead the Annex 1 forces. </i>

00:05:40.538 --> 00:05:46.410 position:5% line:71% align:start
 <i>Most have military backgrounds.</i>
 <i>But they are far more than</i>
 <i>simple mutated-cockroach</i>
 <i>killers. </i>

00:05:50.549 --> 00:05:55.255 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>They come from Japan...</i>
 <i>Gerrmany... China...</i>

00:05:56.089 --> 00:06:01.262 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>America... Russia... and the </i>
 <i>Roman Federation.</i>

00:06:01.962 --> 00:06:06.767 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>These brave men and women... are</i>
 <i>anti-terraformar specialists.</i>

00:06:08.502 --> 00:06:10.238 position:21% line:89% align:start
[angered breathing]

00:06:10.272 --> 00:06:12.275 position:7% line:83% align:start
So, you two have made it this
far.

00:06:12.574 --> 00:06:14.342 position:10% line:83% align:start
You've got guts, that's for
sure.

00:06:14.877 --> 00:06:15.377 position:38% line:89% align:start
Captain!

00:06:15.978 --> 00:06:17.146 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'll take it from here.

00:06:17.880 --> 00:06:19.448 position:7% line:89% align:start
Head to the escape vehilcles.

00:06:25.321 --> 00:06:26.523 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sigh]

00:06:30.228 --> 00:06:32.462 position:7% line:83% align:start
(MICHELLE) <i>Apparently they've </i>
 <i>nfiltrated other areas, too.</i>

00:06:33.398 --> 00:06:37.269 position:5% line:5% align:start
Joe and Liu, head to the living
quarters.  Asimov, cargo hold.

00:06:37.303 --> 00:06:40.472 position:5% line:5% align:start
Adolf, you should go and watch
over the escape vehicles in the
hangar.

00:06:44.543 --> 00:06:48.081 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>This is Shokichi Komachi,</i>
 <i>captain of the Annex 1.</i>

00:06:48.615 --> 00:06:50.318 position:21% line:89% align:start
Initiate Plan Delta

00:06:51.886 --> 00:06:55.489 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>The main engine is down. We're </i>
 <i>rapidly descending toward</i>
 <i>Mars's surface. </i>

00:06:58.994 --> 00:07:05.834 position:5% line:71% align:start
 <i>All personnel head to the escape</i>
 <i>vehicle dock immediately. And</i>
 <i>brace yourselves. It's going to</i>
 <i>be a rough landing.  </i>

00:07:06.102 --> 00:07:07.337 position:24% line:89% align:start
[grunts and sighs]

00:07:07.369 --> 00:07:11.074 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Terraformar yelling]

00:07:11.107 --> 00:07:12.408 position:44% line:89% align:start
huh?

00:07:12.642 --> 00:07:14.311 position:27% line:89% align:start
[barking calls]

00:07:14.345 --> 00:07:15.179 position:16% line:89% align:start
(JOSEPH) You're alright now.

00:07:21.552 --> 00:07:23.188 position:13% line:89% align:start
You all, leave this to me.

00:07:23.688 --> 00:07:25.357 position:16% line:89% align:start
Get to the escape pods.

00:07:27.092 --> 00:07:28.526 position:16% line:89% align:start
(SYLVESTER) <i>Ah, Captain.</i>

00:07:29.661 --> 00:07:34.368 position:16% line:83% align:start
We should get go- Oh! I see
you've got your hands full.

00:07:36.036 --> 00:07:36.904 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckle]

00:07:46.014 --> 00:07:47.982 position:30% line:89% align:start
Hey, not cool.

00:07:48.016 --> 00:07:52.388 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chirping]

00:07:57.160 --> 00:07:59.262 position:13% line:83% align:start
(JOSEPH) Your buddies are
smudging up the glass.

00:07:59.996 --> 00:08:01.564 position:7% line:83% align:start
You know how hard that is to
clean?

00:08:02.132 --> 00:08:04.501 position:5% line:83% align:start
[heavy breathing] Everyone, stay
calm!

00:08:05.069 --> 00:08:06.971 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>The escape vehicles are just </i>
 <i>ahead.</i>

00:08:07.004 --> 00:08:08.272 position:7% line:89% align:start
[panting and heavy breathing]

00:08:09.407 --> 00:08:10.174 position:30% line:89% align:start
(AKARI) <i>Wait!</i>

00:08:10.207 --> 00:08:11.209 position:33% line:89% align:start
Stop, Alex!

00:08:11.243 --> 00:08:12.009 position:38% line:89% align:start
Huh...?

00:08:12.043 --> 00:08:13.245 position:30% line:89% align:start
Marcos! Akari!

00:08:13.744 --> 00:08:15.579 position:13% line:89% align:start
[gasp] You guys are safe!

00:08:17.516 --> 00:08:20.286 position:5% line:83% align:start
(AKARI) The captain said there
might be roaches in there, too.

00:08:21.453 --> 00:08:22.922 position:19% line:89% align:start
Everyone, stand back!

00:08:32.166 --> 00:08:33.934 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:08:38.073 --> 00:08:38.940 position:30% line:89% align:start
Watch closely.

00:08:42.178 --> 00:08:43.179 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:08:52.456 --> 00:08:55.625 position:30% line:89% align:start
[weak moaning]

00:09:02.800 --> 00:09:04.002 position:38% line:89% align:start
Vermin.

00:09:07.339 --> 00:09:08.607 position:41% line:89% align:start
Woah.

00:09:09.341 --> 00:09:10.477 position:21% line:89% align:start
(AKARI) <i>Impressive.</i>

00:09:20.720 --> 00:09:21.989 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckle]

00:09:34.770 --> 00:09:37.507 position:5% line:83% align:start
Seems that six roaches were able
to sneak onboard....

00:09:39.609 --> 00:09:42.346 position:5% line:5% align:start
 <i>And we've got exactly six</i>
 <i>officers on the ship...</i>

00:09:48.719 --> 00:09:52.290 position:27% line:89% align:start
[crew murmering]

00:09:52.524 --> 00:09:53.358 position:30% line:89% align:start
(ADOLF) <i>Eva...</i>

00:09:53.391 --> 00:09:54.393 position:44% line:89% align:start
huh?

00:09:55.528 --> 00:09:56.861 position:24% line:89% align:start
(ADOLF) <i>Careful...</i>

00:09:56.895 --> 00:09:59.398 position:30% line:89% align:start
tears can be dangerous.

00:09:59.832 --> 00:10:02.369 position:27% line:89% align:start
[gasp] Yes sir.

00:10:02.835 --> 00:10:05.505 position:33% line:89% align:start
[quiet sobs]

00:10:05.539 --> 00:10:08.375 position:13% line:89% align:start
All hands... Atten...hut!

00:10:10.143 --> 00:10:14.282 position:5% line:83% align:start
I suppose I could ramble on and
on, but this says it all!

00:10:14.315 --> 00:10:15.216 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:10:16.851 --> 00:10:21.390 position:5% line:77% align:start
Captain Komachi will brief you
on the operation. Everybody
listen up, got it?

00:10:25.161 --> 00:10:32.068 position:7% line:71% align:start
(SHOKICHI) <i>In accordance with </i>
 <i>emergency Plan Delta, we will</i>
 <i>now commence landing on Mars</i>
 <i>using the six escape vehicles.</i>

00:10:33.370 --> 00:10:36.240 position:5% line:89% align:start
I will be in charge of Squad 1.

00:10:37.408 --> 00:10:41.580 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>Michelle will lead Squad 2, the</i>
 <i>other Japanese and American</i>
 <i>squad.</i>

00:10:42.247 --> 00:10:46.552 position:7% line:77% align:start
 <i>The Russian and Scandinavian </i>
 <i>group, Squad 3, will be led by</i>
 <i>Asimov.</i>

00:10:47.553 --> 00:10:50.590 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>Squad 4, from China and Asia,</i>
 <i>by Liu.</i>

00:10:51.757 --> 00:10:55.429 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>Squad 5, from Germany and South</i>
 <i>America, Adolf.</i>

00:10:56.762 --> 00:10:59.766 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>Squad 6, from Europe and Africa,</i>
 <i>Joseph.</i>

00:11:02.237 --> 00:11:05.273 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>To avoid ambush, we will launch</i>
 <i>in different directions.</i>

00:11:06.808 --> 00:11:11.779 position:7% line:77% align:start
We'll communicate via radio.
Once we land, rendezvous at the
main ship.

00:11:12.248 --> 00:11:12.882 position:38% line:89% align:start
 <i>Got it?</i>

00:11:12.915 --> 00:11:14.116 position:27% line:89% align:start
(CREW) Yes, sir!

00:11:14.917 --> 00:11:16.118 position:21% line:89% align:start
(SHOKICHI) Let's go.

00:11:17.920 --> 00:11:21.791 position:27% line:89% align:start
[crew murmering]

00:11:22.627 --> 00:11:24.629 position:19% line:89% align:start
Sheila... you guys...

00:11:26.663 --> 00:11:30.801 position:7% line:71% align:start
We'll be okay, Eva. We're in
different squads, but the
officers leading us through this
are tough.

00:11:31.436 --> 00:11:32.304 position:44% line:89% align:start
Mhm

00:11:35.507 --> 00:11:36.508 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckle]

00:11:41.247 --> 00:11:42.482 position:7% line:89% align:start
(AKARI) <i>Be careful out there.</i>

00:11:48.355 --> 00:11:49.590 position:35% line:89% align:start
Alright...

00:11:49.623 --> 00:11:50.824 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>see you on Mars!</i>

00:12:48.023 --> 00:12:49.591 position:35% line:89% align:start
[hissing]

00:13:26.633 --> 00:13:28.435 position:7% line:89% align:start
No sign of roaches out there.

00:13:28.703 --> 00:13:29.437 position:35% line:89% align:start
Move out.

00:13:42.851 --> 00:13:44.788 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:13:51.629 --> 00:13:52.630 position:27% line:89% align:start
(YAEKO) <i>I've...</i>

00:13:54.198 --> 00:13:57.803 position:7% line:77% align:start
...seen so many photographs of
Mars taken back in the twentieth
century, but

00:13:59.103 --> 00:14:01.306 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>they looked nothing like this.</i>

00:14:03.475 --> 00:14:05.678 position:5% line:83% align:start
(ALEX) <i>A lot can change in five </i>
 <i>hundred years.</i>

00:14:07.814 --> 00:14:10.483 position:5% line:83% align:start
(AKARI) <i>It's... almost a </i>
 <i>paradise.</i>

00:14:19.893 --> 00:14:24.366 position:5% line:77% align:start
Quit acting like tourists, you
idiots! It's not a sightseeing
trip.

00:14:24.699 --> 00:14:27.001 position:5% line:83% align:start
Check it out. We're lucky we
landed near some water.

00:14:28.504 --> 00:14:33.509 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>The ice in the soil has begun to</i>
 <i>melt, but Mars has nowhere near</i>
 <i>the water Earth does. </i>

00:14:33.909 --> 00:14:36.346 position:5% line:83% align:start
Should we check it? See if it's
drinkable?

00:14:36.713 --> 00:14:43.019 position:13% line:77% align:start
Yes. We have enough water
onboard to last only forty days.
The more we have, the better.

00:14:43.688 --> 00:14:45.857 position:5% line:83% align:start
Besides, ladies have thier needs
too.

00:14:46.624 --> 00:14:47.692 position:44% line:89% align:start
Do you see a lady?

00:14:48.526 --> 00:14:49.093 position:38% line:89% align:start
Well...

00:14:50.128 --> 00:14:51.129 position:30% line:89% align:start
Oh!... Uh!...

00:14:52.297 --> 00:14:55.501 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'll contact the other squads.
Stay alert, both of you.

00:14:55.534 --> 00:14:58.036 position:10% line:83% align:start
You never know where these
pieces of shit might be hiding.

00:14:59.472 --> 00:15:00.740 position:30% line:89% align:start
Y-yes, Ma'am!

00:15:02.976 --> 00:15:06.714 position:10% line:89% align:start
[deep breaths through mask]

00:15:11.552 --> 00:15:13.722 position:7% line:5% align:start
It's safe. Masks off everyone.

00:15:15.724 --> 00:15:17.559 position:30% line:89% align:start
[deep breath]

00:15:17.760 --> 00:15:19.896 position:5% line:89% align:start
Oh wow, I can actually breathe!

00:15:20.696 --> 00:15:24.567 position:7% line:77% align:start
I heard the air here, is
actually the same as in the
Andes.

00:15:24.902 --> 00:15:28.739 position:10% line:83% align:start
This is amazing. Another perk
from the procedure, you tlhink?

00:15:32.509 --> 00:15:37.582 position:7% line:5% align:start
 <i>Damnit! Theres not much serum.</i>
 <i>We were never supposed to leave</i>
 <i>Annex 1.  </i>

00:15:38.082 --> 00:15:39.919 position:10% line:5% align:start
All we've got are emergancy
spares.

00:15:44.590 --> 00:15:47.894 position:10% line:83% align:start
I wonder if the others have
landed too.

00:15:48.762 --> 00:15:50.095 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>I hope everyone's okay...</i>

00:15:56.002 --> 00:15:57.003 position:38% line:89% align:start
Well...

00:15:58.138 --> 00:16:00.775 position:16% line:83% align:start
I can't see that much but I
think we escaped the ambush.

00:16:01.209 --> 00:16:02.210 position:5% line:89% align:start
Yeah...

00:16:09.953 --> 00:16:10.954 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm

00:16:13.523 --> 00:16:16.659 position:5% line:83% align:start
Squad 2 reporting. Michelle K.
Davis here.

00:16:17.260 --> 00:16:19.797 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>All other squads report your </i>
 <i>status. Over.</i>

00:16:21.097 --> 00:16:26.103 position:5% line:77% align:start
(JOSEPH) Whoa, Michelle's quick.
They must be close. We're still
about...

00:16:28.974 --> 00:16:30.041 position:27% line:89% align:start
What the hell?!

00:16:30.075 --> 00:16:30.775 position:33% line:89% align:start
[struggling]

00:16:31.443 --> 00:16:34.179 position:10% line:89% align:start
Woah...Ah! [heavy breathing]

00:16:34.680 --> 00:16:35.982 position:27% line:89% align:start
[crew panicking]

00:16:37.216 --> 00:16:38.518 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:16:48.028 --> 00:16:54.703 position:7% line:89% align:start
[heavy breathing and groaning]

00:17:00.776 --> 00:17:02.012 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:17:04.346 --> 00:17:08.218 position:16% line:71% align:start
(JOSEPH) <i>Oh, boy... Just</i>
 <i>great...  Well, I suppose at</i>
 <i>least one of our ships was bound</i>
 <i>to get attacked... </i>

00:17:11.856 --> 00:17:14.191 position:7% line:83% align:start
Guess we drew the short straw
this time.

00:17:16.661 --> 00:17:21.199 position:7% line:71% align:start
 <i>I heard intelligent life had </i>
 <i>been found here as far back as</i>
 <i>20 years ago. But I never</i>
 <i>expected this. </i>

00:17:22.234 --> 00:17:24.136 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckle]

00:17:24.671 --> 00:17:29.609 position:5% line:5% align:start
We've flown seriously far by
now. The other squads must be
long gone.

00:17:29.642 --> 00:17:34.147 position:5% line:77% align:start
[chuckle] Of course. Elena, just
what exactly are our
coordinates now?

00:17:35.883 --> 00:17:36.817 position:5% line:89% align:start
How the hell would I know that?!

00:17:38.252 --> 00:17:42.824 position:7% line:5% align:start
The satellite's down, and we
have no reference points to go
by! But...

00:17:43.090 --> 00:17:45.061 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>this sure looks right to me...</i>

00:17:46.361 --> 00:17:47.897 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>We've done it sir.</i>

00:17:48.798 --> 00:17:51.734 position:13% line:83% align:start
[chuckle] Yes indeed. Just as
planned.

00:17:55.839 --> 00:17:57.574 position:7% line:83% align:start
(SYLVESTER) <i>And that's touch </i>
 <i>down!</i>

00:18:06.184 --> 00:18:07.251 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:18:07.285 --> 00:18:08.754 position:5% line:89% align:start
They really do exist.

00:18:09.253 --> 00:18:11.023 position:7% line:83% align:start
They are quite a sight aren't
they?

00:18:12.725 --> 00:18:17.097 position:5% line:77% align:start
You'd think there'd be swarms of
cockroaches here. Not that I'm
complaining, mind you.

00:18:18.163 --> 00:18:21.635 position:7% line:83% align:start
Alright. Enough chitchat. Our
mission awaits us.

00:18:22.069 --> 00:18:23.104 position:19% line:89% align:start
[grunt amd moaning in pain]

00:18:23.971 --> 00:18:25.973 position:19% line:89% align:start
[chirping and hissing]

00:18:26.007 --> 00:18:27.008 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:18:27.041 --> 00:18:28.042 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chirping]

00:18:28.743 --> 00:18:29.243 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:18:33.949 --> 00:18:34.816 position:35% line:89% align:start
[hissing]

00:18:36.119 --> 00:18:37.120 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:18:38.755 --> 00:18:40.823 position:24% line:89% align:start
[heavy breathing]

00:18:42.025 --> 00:18:44.061 position:7% line:83% align:start
Somehow they slipped past our
radar.

00:18:44.794 --> 00:18:46.964 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>It's like they came out of thin</i>
 <i>air.</i>

00:18:49.299 --> 00:18:51.970 position:7% line:83% align:start
[chuckle] Just one? How very
amusing.

00:18:52.804 --> 00:18:55.006 position:5% line:89% align:start
Elena! We're going with Sign B!

00:18:55.339 --> 00:18:55.974 position:41% line:89% align:start
Right!

00:18:56.741 --> 00:18:57.642 position:7% line:89% align:start
(SYLVESTER) <i>Bring out the net!</i>

00:19:01.147 --> 00:19:03.349 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>It's just one so save the serum.</i>

00:19:03.983 --> 00:19:07.988 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>Remember your training. I want </i>
 <i>this bastard brought in alive!</i>

00:19:08.387 --> 00:19:11.158 position:13% line:83% align:start
Leave the shooting to me!
Follow my lead.

00:19:12.459 --> 00:19:13.660 position:44% line:5% align:start
Sis!

00:19:15.462 --> 00:19:19.000 position:5% line:77% align:start
You or the captain would blast
its head off. And we're on a
mission, so don't call me "Sis!"

00:19:20.234 --> 00:19:20.902 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:19:24.740 --> 00:19:29.344 position:7% line:5% align:start
 <i>It's heading straight for her </i>
 <i>just as he said it would. But...</i>

00:19:30.847 --> 00:19:32.314 position:7% line:89% align:start
(SYLVESTER) <i>Concentrate, Ivan.</i>

00:19:34.017 --> 00:19:38.354 position:5% line:77% align:start
Hold on to that serum. As long
as the roach is heading towards
Elena, we'll be okay.

00:19:39.490 --> 00:19:47.398 position:5% line:71% align:start
 <i>Believe you me, she's the best </i>
 <i>shot in the North Sea! And with</i>
 <i>an anti-terraformar net</i>
 <i>launcher, she's unstoppable. </i>

00:19:50.469 --> 00:19:51.703 position:30% line:89% align:start
Terraformar...

00:19:55.174 --> 00:19:56.175 position:38% line:89% align:start
 <i>Locked!</i>

00:20:09.891 --> 00:20:10.892 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:20:12.327 --> 00:20:13.328 position:30% line:89% align:start
[shaky breath]

00:20:32.950 --> 00:20:35.753 position:10% line:89% align:start
The radar's clear... right.

00:20:42.361 --> 00:20:43.428 position:27% line:89% align:start
Let's move out.

00:20:49.569 --> 00:20:51.806 position:5% line:89% align:start
Everyone, let me say this again.

00:20:52.139 --> 00:20:57.279 position:5% line:77% align:start
Now that Plan Delta is in place,
a rescue vessel from Earth
should be on its way.

00:20:58.113 --> 00:21:05.288 position:5% line:71% align:start
In forty days, it will land here
on Mars to take us home. In the
meantime, you have two
sub-missions...

00:21:06.588 --> 00:21:10.294 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>First, regroup at the Annex 1</i>
 <i>crash site.</i>

00:21:11.594 --> 00:21:16.834 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>Once there, restore the research</i>
 <i>equipment, and prepare to</i>
 <i>return with virus samples. </i>

00:21:17.467 --> 00:21:19.971 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>And the second mission is... </i>
 <i>stay alive!</i>

00:21:21.471 --> 00:21:24.475 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>For now... we'll regroup with</i>
 <i>Michelle and Squad 2.</i>

00:21:25.977 --> 00:21:30.583 position:5% line:77% align:start
Once we join up with the other
senior officers, we'll retrieve
Annex 1!

00:21:30.916 --> 00:21:31.917 position:33% line:89% align:start
Understood?

00:21:32.418 --> 00:21:33.419 position:44% line:5% align:start
Yes!

00:21:34.120 --> 00:21:37.591 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>(NARRATOR) April 12th, AD 2620</i>

00:21:38.625 --> 00:21:41.162 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>The research team lands on Mars.</i>

00:21:43.496 --> 00:21:49.670 position:7% line:77% align:start
 <i>The hunt for the Alien Engine</i>
 <i>Virus, and the fight against</i>
 <i>the terraformars, has begun.</i>

00:21:49.704 --> 00:21:52.207 position:19% line:89% align:start
[chirping and hissing]

00:21:59.349 --> 00:22:02.018 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>Forty days now stand between our</i>
 <i>heros...</i>

00:22:03.987 --> 00:22:05.089 position:19% line:89% align:start
[clicking and hissing]

00:22:05.122 --> 00:22:06.357 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>...and rescue.</i>

00:22:07.523 --> 00:22:08.525 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:22:10.195 --> 00:22:12.197 position:10% line:83% align:start
(TERRAFORMARS) [screams and
hissing]

00:23:43.066 --> 00:23:47.104 position:27% line:83% align:start
to be continued
